{
  "text": "First, the training dataset was scaled to place it in the 14-dimensional unit box [0, [CITATION_1] 14 . Then, the same scaling was applied to the testing datasets T = T mon \u222a . . . \u222a T f ri . Application of Algorithm 4 to the training set X , using the Gaussian kernel from Eq. 4.1 with \u03b5 = 0.6, t = 1 and \u00b5 = 10 \u22127 , produced an s-dimensional 2\u00b5 distortion of the first time step \u03a8 (1) of DM of X , h [CITATION_2] s : X \u2192 R s with s = 138. The neighborhood size parameter \u03b5 was chosen to be twice the median of all the mutual distances between the data points in R 14 . Such a selection is a common heuristic for determining this parameter in DM context. This concludes the training phase.",
  "correct_citation": {
